iconAttributes.iconText: Roberto enjoyed double success in the summer of 2002, both on the domestic and international stage. The first triumph came as ‘El Hombre Bala’ assisted both goals as Real Madrid beat Leverkusen 2-1 in the Champions League final. Later that summer, Roberto would help Brazil to go one step further than they had 4 years earlier, as they lifted the 2002 FIFA World Cup™. His performances throughout 2002 led to a Ballon d’Or nomination, finishing runner-up, and a place in the UEFA Team of the Year.

Paolo Maldini rose through the ranks at Milan and quickly cemented his first-team place. Initially starting out at right-back before moving to left-back to complement his fantastic left foot, Maldini was part of one of the strongest defences in history. During the 1987-88 season, Maldini won his first trophy with Milan in a dominant Serie A title win, during which they conceded just 14 goals all season. 1988 also saw him make his international debut for Italy, the first of 126 appearances.
